body_html:
@kate-kate XCode is the conglomerate that contains XCode command line tool and SDK.

I just installed and compiled TensorFlow using the following command without error:

bazel test -c opt -- //tensorflow/... -//tensorflow/compiler/... -//tensorflow/contrib/lite/...

bazel: 0.17.1
TensorFlow: 1.10.0
OSX: 10.13.5

One thing you would need to check though, make sure this folder is not empty: /private/var/tmp/_bazel_kate/8be913d8cdea6dd8174f0dac0a48c277/external/double_conversion. You may need to download the zip file from https://github.com/google/double-conversion/archive and manually move it there.

body:
@kate-kate XCode is the conglomerate that contains XCode command line tool and SDK.

I just installed and compiled TensorFlow using the following command without error:
```
bazel test -c opt -- //tensorflow/... -//tensorflow/compiler/... -//tensorflow/contrib/lite/...

bazel: 0.17.1
TensorFlow: 1.10.0
OSX: 10.13.5
```
One thing you would need to check though, make sure this folder is not empty: `/private/var/tmp/_bazel_kate/8be913d8cdea6dd8174f0dac0a48c277/external/double_conversion`. You may need to download the zip file from `https://github.com/google/double-conversion/archive` and manually move it there.
